children: The Office Story: That's what the data said
Analyzing character stats,relationships and their influence on popularity of
The Office TV show through interactive visualizations using Plotly,d3graph
and chord packages.
Source: Giphy, The Office GIF By NBC
Presented by Swarnita Venkatraman

(b) Goal-To determine what kind of questions can be answered from the show's script and ratings data analysis that can lead the makers to better data-driven decisions while investing in a potential revival/reboot.
(a)Performed data pre-processing, feature engineering and data analysis on the show's dialogues dataset from theofficequotes.net and IMDB ratings dataset from Kaggle.

Question 4:
In depth analysis of the four major character relationships
over 9 seasonsHow do they influence theratings?

The four character relationships seem to be in focus between season 25(though a dip seen in season 4 is possibly because it had only 14 episodes) after which their share of lines and scenes decrease with the focus shifting to newly introduced character story arcs when Michael leaves the show in season 7.
Since the R values are also very less for all 4 pairs, the total lines spoken by them do not significantly affect the ratings.

Question 5:

Michaels good ratings range and high median rating confirms his role as the central character to retain continuity in episodes while after his departure season 8 and 9s erratic plotlines and ratings dip can be linked to Andy and Dwights high lines andlow ratings range.
Question 6:
Exploration of Female representation in theshow-
Did the female characters get their due with respect to the number of linesspoken?

Female characters do not have a major share of lines in episodes meant to be centered around women like Sexual Harassment (24%), Boys and Girls (40%) and Womens appreciation (31%); considering half the episodes of the show lie in the 2550% lines category

Amongst the season-wise highest percentage of lines episodes, female characters had maximum lines in just two episodes Erin in Secretarys day and Pam in Lice(this was also the only episode where the 50% of lines mark is crossed).
Source : Giphy,Season 1 Nbc GIF By The Office
An Office revival/reboot may or may not be on cards but successful analysis of a shows ratings,script and character stats(arcs and relationships) enables better data-driven
decision making for the makers to identify and invest confidently in what the viewers
prefer and whatmore would they like to see in a revival/reboot.
